The evidence with the title 'Drone industry delight at new US rules - BBC News ' says Jun 22, 2016  ... The rules regarding flying drones in the United States are relaxed by the US Federal Aviation Authority .  ... The regulations state that commercial drones can be flown as long as the pilot is over the age of 16 , has the drone in his or her line of sight , and does not elevate to over 400 feet above ground level . 
